      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T21:44:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, I take that back.  No array underflow.  This is somewhat accidentally working as intended and I\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s a neat feature to double down on or something very subtly confusing I should prevent.\n\nA while back we added the type F32a to allow passing either an F32 or a float as an argument to almost all skvm::Builder methods and operators, where the float is auto-splatted.  It just so happens that the way F32a is structured, if you construct it with F32{}, it\u0027ll act as if it were constructed with 0.0f!\n\n(All the same applies to I32/int/I32a and splat(0).)",
